definition.value: An organoiodine compound that is benzene substituted by 4-hydroxyphenoxy, iodo, and 2-aminoethyl groups at positions 1, 2, and 4, respectively. It is a thyroid hormone metabolite and a potent agonist of trace amine-associated receptor 1.
An alkene that is dodecane containing one double bond at position 1. It is an intermediate used in the production of lubricants and surfactants.
A cycloalkane that consists of fourteen carbons each bonded with two hydrogens.
A butyrate ester resulting from the formal condensation of the hydroxy group of propanol with the carboxy group of butyric acid.
A phosphatidylcholine 16:0_16:1 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are palmitoleoyl and palmitoyl respectively.
